Open command prompt and get to your project location.
Example: cd C:\workspace\Module9>

ant clean 
ant compile 
ant run
ant makexsltreports

Now open a notepad copy the commands that you usually use to run the program through ANT.

1. cd C:\workspace\Module9>
2. ant clean compile run makexsltreports

Now save the above notepad file in double quotes like "MY_TEST_SUITE.bat" and save it on the desktop.

Now close the command prompt and just double click on the MY_TEST_SUITE.bat file.

It will start executing your programs through bat file irrespective of the bat file location.